    "body": "What is the reasoning for turning on the cxx wrappers always when openmpi has turned them off by default?  This should be off by default... and enabled via a variant?\r\n\r\nFrom the openmpi/package.py:\r\n        if spec.satisfies('@2.0:'):\r\n            # for Open-MPI 2.0:, C++ bindings are disabled by default.\r\n            config_args.extend(['--enable-mpi-cxx'])\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Spack version\r\n\r\n```console\r\n$ spack --version\r\n0.14.0-206-e916a9424\r\n```\r\n",
